I've been using this app for awhile and it always played an .mp3 file to the end and looped it if you selected loop.Now it just shuts off after 10 minutes of a 32 minute audio .mp3 I keep playing.It also never registers itself on Android as an audio player and it's impossible to select it as the .mp3 player for your phone.It never comes up on the "open with" menu and now with Android 10 ,in settings, installed apps, MSC, open by default all options are greyed out.This is a disaster.

A decent app that does as professed. I have three pro versions: iPod, Kindle, Galaxy. Mostly I use the speed adjustment to slow down riffs. I also accelerate rhythm tracks when I nail the riff. Pitch is helpful to play in a different scale. A zoom feature would be nice, but for lack of that, a portion of the song can be saved, then opened. This app is as good as it gets, although I haven't researched alternatives.
Why did they get rid of the repeat function??? I need this function back!

Edit: this won't let me load a single file in to it. It makes me load a whole folder every time causing my library to just be a bunch of duplicates. Will be 5 stars once this is fixed. You can loop sections, slow down in real time, change pitch, and export as an MP3. Easy to use!
great way to learn how to play songs on whatever instrument. So easy to set loop points, change tempo, and learn every note of a specific part of a song.
great app been uses for years

This app was the best out there and i had it since 2014 and now this year this month when I started using it on my Samsung Galaxy s10 the music will play and then shut off on lock screen. I never experienced this before, I thought it was my settings on my phone. But if it could be updated to where it was working on and off screen again I will definitely give it a 5 star rating.

had this app for a while and i love it. only issue that started recently is that music keeps cutting out of phone is locked but starts up again after unlocking. never had this issue before. please fix. other than that great app UPDATE: App has been updated but still having the same issue. It just suddenly stopped loading files, even though it's been working great for literally years. So, it would have gotten a five except is on the blink. Hopefully it'll be back soon!

nice app to change to the tone u want

Strangely, this app has really helped with my depression. I love music, and "re-discovering" some of my favourite songs by slowing them down or changing the pitch. It makes me smile more often than not, and shows me the reason as to why I love music. Probably not what you intended with this app, but thanks.  Just some suggestions if you were looking - Playlist Integration  - Choose to crop out multiple parts of a song rather than just the start and end - Option to manually change tags of audio when saving (Title change, Artist Info etc...)  - More user-friendly UI for the "Main Menu" of Songs you have  Thanks again!

I use this app very often for music practicing. It is the best I know. Selection, looping, speed changes, it all works smooth. I would really like a zoom feature though to make selections easier in larger recordings. Also the file access interface is a joke. If you open the same file 10 times, it appears 10 times in the list... I use a file manager to start the app with the file I want to use. But really cool otherwise. Thanks for this great app!
This is the best app of its type I have used and I have tried a lot of them.

Make the pitch change up and down buttons much finer resolution since musicians are usually trying to get the song they are learning from up or down to standard pitch which is usually something less than one tone. Thanks!
